      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issue] Line 586: Changing the generic setAccountsActive(false) semantics so non-proxy accounts always remain active may affect existing callers that expect this method to actually deactivate all accounts, for example during shutdown, network state changes, or explicit account lifecycle operations. The new behavior is specific to background push optimization, so it should not be hidden behind this broad API. Add a dedicated method or parameter for background deactivation and keep setAccountsActive preserving its previous contract.\n```suggestion\nfun setAccountsActive(active: Boolean) {\n    mExecutor.execute {\n        Log.i(TAG, \"setAccountsActive() running… $active\")\n        for (a in mAccountList) {\n            JamiService.setAccountActive(a.accountId, active || a.isDhtProxyEnabled)\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfun setAccountsActiveForBackground(active: Boolean) {\n    mExecutor.execute {\n        Log.i(TAG, \"setAccountsActiveForBackground() running… $active\")\n        for (a in mAccountList) {\n            JamiService.setAccountActive(a.accountId, active || !a.isDhtProxyEnabled)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```",
